<L>__{exterior cinema day david's p.o.v.}
<A>__{there stands jack, now truly rotted and ghastly. he's pretty much dried out, a third of his face gone revealing the grinning skull. he waves to david. jack points inside the theater and goes in. david smiles, walks across the intersection, and up to the box office.}
<C>__{ticket lady}
<D>__{two and a half quid, please.}
<A>__{david reaches in his pocket. all he has are traveler's checks.}
<C>__{david}
<D>__{will you take a traveler's check?}
<C>__{ticket lady}
<D>__{no, sorry.}
<A>__{david signs a $100 check and hands it to her.}
<C>__{david}
<D>__{keep the change.}
<C>__{ticket lady}
<D>__{well, thank you, sir!}
<A>__{she gives him a ticket. david goes in.}
